sentences: Amit Peled (born 1973) is an Israeli-American cellist, conductor, and pedagogue.
He plays Pablo Casals's 1733 Matteo Goffriller cello.
His third CD with Centaur Records "Reflections" was released in September 2012.
He also has been named Music Director for CityMusic Cleveland for the 2019-2020 season.
Prior to Casals's cello, Peled played a 1689 Andrea Guarneri cello.
Peled was a student of Bernard Greenhouse and is now a sought-after pedagogue of cello at Peabody Institute and when hired, was the youngest professor at a top musical institution.
